    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>You Call Them Sundaes?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Amy Sharry letter comments on July 5 article on ice cream sundaes (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The ice cream sundaes represented in ''Inspiration in a Tall, Cool Glass'' (July 5) were truly heroic and masterpieces in their own right, but not exactly what I consider a sundae (with Village's version being the exception). It was as if you had asked fashion designers to redesign the American flag with the results being three-color flags lacking red, white, blue, stars and stripes.</p>
        <p>AMY SHARRY  Madison, N.J.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
